  "doc_id": "7281",
  "text": "The prevalence of functional faecal incontinence has been found to vary between 1 and 4% in children > 4 years old and between 1 and 2% in 7-year-old children. The rate in children aged 10 and 11 years was found to be 1.6%. This condition was observed three to six times more often in boys than in girls (3:1 to 6:1) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
